        text: "Jack Airs is an opinion columnist for The Sunday View newspaper. Last week Jack submitted an article for publication to the editor of the newspaper about John Dormer, a leading politician. The proposed article contained the following paragraph. Dormer is a politician with little done and less to do. That won't stop him from clawing his way into a position of power well above that to which he is entitled. But incompetence is the least of Dormer's crimes. I have it on good authority that Dormer has for years pushed legislation that has benefited companies in which he has a financial interest. I believe that a survey of his bank account over the last ten years appear more suited to that of a drug dealer than an honest politician. As for his family life, I know for a fact that there is no point in asking Dormer's wife where he spends his nights in Dublin. Better to ask well known homosexual restaurant owner Ricardo. John Dormer is unfit for public office. The paragraph concludes with Jack Airs' standard sign off line that he uses at the end of every one of his articles: This is just one man's opinion. The editor of the Sunday View was concerned about the piece and sent a draft copy to the deader of Dormer's political party and Dormer's wife for their comments before deciding whether or not to publish the item. In the meantime, Jack Air included the paragraph on his personal blog, which is hosted on the Sunday View newspaper website. Advise the Sunday View if they have any defences to a defamation action by Dormer against them.",
