        text: "Jenny works for Head Ltd which sells homeopathic remedies based on ancient traditions. Until about 18 months ago, business was rather sedate, mostly from the older generation who were looking for remedies for certain ailments such as arthritis. However in recent times, another group of customers has emerged who have realised that these herbs can also be used to alter their mood in a manner similar to alcohol and drugs. As word spread, the clientele became very different: far more aggressive and Jenny began to feel unsafe. In particular, Jenny had complained to her manager that customers were now hanging around the back entrance of the shop when she was putting out the rubbish from the shop and were scaring her. Her manager said that she should simply toughen as they were now making lots of money but he did promise to put in some CCTV cameras, which he duly did. Nonetheless she still felt unsafe and the CCTV cameras seemed not to be acting as a deterrent. One day Jenny was so scared that when she came back in she never locked the door behind her. Keith, seeing his chance, followed her in and stole an amount of herbs from the stockroom. Jenny's manager was incensed and introduced a self-closing and locking door to the back which could only be opened by way of a key. Keith was arrested and sent to prison for 3 months. One day during that three month period, Jenny went out the back entrance but forgot her key. When she tried to get back in and could not, some of the people outside beat here severely. Advise Jenny if she has any claim in tort against Head Ltd.",
