        text: "Ellen is a financial investment salesperson who works on her own and relies on commission earned from her sales. Ellen has a regular client list which she normally calls on an annual basis, but in recent times she has taken new clients given the downturn in the economy. On Friday Ellen received a telephone call from a recent client, Philip, asking her to meet him at his house urgently. Philip told her that he had come into a large sum of money that he was seeking to invest. When Ellen arrived at Philip's house later that night, he opened the door and brought her into the living room. Ellen opened her briefcase expecting to show Philip some new investment opportunities when suddenly Philip flew into a temper and began shouting and screaming at her, saying that he had lost his life savings as a result of following her advice. He said that he wanted his money back right now and wanted a cheque for €40000. Ellen felt scared, and got up to go at which point Philip also stood up and said \"You need to think twice before leaving this room without giving me my money!\" Ellen sat down scared. Philip continued to pace around the room explaining how much money he had lost, what it meant to him and how he had to make her pay to 'even things up'. As Ellen became increasingly more scared, she resolved to leave immediately. She stood up and began to walk towards the door. Philip was now shouting loudly as he moved to intercept her exit, saying \"Oh you want to go eh? Let me open the door and leave you scurry off like the vermin you are!\" Ellen panicked and swung her bag at Philip hitting him in the jaw. Unfortunately Ellen's laptop was in her bag and Philip's jaw was broken in three places. Ellen has now received a claim from Philip for the injuries he suffered. Advise Ellen as to her potential legal liability in tort law.",
