        examType: 'Problem',
        description:
          'Daniel is a well-known financial advisor. Advise Mary if she has any action in tort against Daniel as a result of his…',
        text: "Daniel is a well-known financial advisor. He has his own radio show where he dispenses advice on investing in stock markets around the world. He also writes numerous articles for newspapers and magazines which are very popular and he has a huge following. In addition, Daniel operates a private consulting firm where for a set fee he offers specific advice on what companies to invest in. Many of his peers have however expressed concerns about his unorthodox views where he often takes a contrarian view to the conventional wisdom which is not based on any real analysis of his own. It is widely believed that Daniel operates on his 'gut' feeling although his success rate compares well with his more traditional competitors. Recently Daniel has taken to Twitter and will tweet various comments designed to attract people to both his radio show and consulting firm. Two weeks ago, Daniel misread a newspaper article which suggested that the European Central Bank would begin raising interest rates rapidly. He figured that if interest rates went up, this would be good for bank profits. Daniel tweeted the following: \"Interest rates going up, banks to profit, buy, buy, buy Provincial Bank shares NOW #makeamillionwithdaniel\" Mary had been following Daniel since he began tweeting and had just come into an inheritance from her deceased mother. She invested it all in Provincial Bank shares as a result of Daniel's tweet. Unfortunately, the ECB had in fact said that they would not raise interest rates rapidly and the share price of all banks fell in value. Provincial Bank suffered more than most and Mary lost about 40% of the value of her investment. Advise Mary if she has any action in tort against Daniel as a result of his actions.",
