          'Michael was a salesperson for CarsRus, a car dealership. Advise CarsRus as to their liability in tort, if any.',
        text: "Michael was a salesperson for CarsRus, a car dealership. He was working one Friday evening by himself when at around 4pm Angela dropped in and said that she was looking for a family minivan at a reasonable price. Michael had several vehicles to show her. Angela really liked one of the minivans that Michael had offered her and wanted to take it for a test drive. However, Angela did not have her driving licence with her and Michael was conscious that due to the pandemic, only one person was allowed in a vehicle at any one time. As a result of this, it was a strict policy of the dealership that no one could take a vehicle for a test drive without leaving a valid driving license. Angela seemed inclined to buy the car but was annoyed that Michael would not let her take it for a test drive and made that annoyance clear to Michael. As Michael was trying to explain to her that his hands were tied on this issue, Angela's husband, Dwight, arrived at the dealership in a panic. He explained that their own car had broken down and that he would now miss his flight because he would not be able to get to the airport in time. Angela now also became very anxious and asked Michael if he could take them to the airport. Michael was hesitant but was also fearful of losing a sale, so he reluctantly agreed. When they went outside, he was surprised to see Angela's two children also waiting. Undeterred Angela insisted that he take all of them to the airport and then demanded that they take the minivan she was interested in and that Angela could use the opportunity to test drive the vehicle. Again, Michael was reluctant, but the logic of Angela's request was compelling. On the way to the airport, while Angela was driving, she injured a pedestrian, Kevin. Advise CarsRus as to their liability in tort, if any.",
