        text: 'Hilary is an alternative therapist who specialises in dealing with various different anxiety and depression issues using unconventional treatments. In particular, she uses what is known as an isolation room that is basically an empty room that is kept in complete and utter darkness. The idea simply put is to remove all external stimuli other than white noise. That sound is played at a volume that is barely perceptible to the human ear. Bill is a patient of Hilary. He is not responding well to the standard treatments for anxiety and depression. As a result, Hilary suggests that he try the isolation room. Bill is concerned that he will feel claustrophobic, but Hilary reassures him that he can ask to be released at any point. Bill agrees to try the isolation room. When Bill is in the room, Hilary starts the white noise. Bill begins to feel sick, and it later transpires that this is not an uncommon side effect of using white noise at that particular volume. Hilary was aware of this but had decided not to tell Bill since she believed the benefits outweighed the risks. Bill now starts shouting that he wishes to leave the room, but Hilary tells him that she will not release him until the time is over. After about 30 minutes, Hilary realizes that it is not working and lets Bill out. Advise Bill as to any action for an intentional tort that he may have against Hilary.',
